              "name": "policy",
              "value": "FAST National University of Computer and Emerging Sciences (FAST-NUCES)  Official Academic Policy and Student Handbook - Administrative Guidelines  1. ATTENDANCE POLICY & EXAMINATION ELIGIBILITY - FAST-NUCES enforces a strict, mandatory 75% minimum attendance policy for all registered undergraduate and graduate courses, including laboratory components. - Any student whose attendance drops below 75% in a specific course will be automatically awarded an \"FA\" grade (Failure due to shortage of Attendance). - A student receiving an FA grade is strictly debarred from sitting for the Final Examination of that course, with zero exceptions.  - CORRESPONDING LABS: Laboratory components are treated as entirely separate 1-credit hour courses. Attendance in labs is tracked independently from the corresponding theoretical course.  2. UNDERGRADUATE GRADING SCALE (HEC 12-GRADE SYSTEM) The university utilizes a fixed-point relative grading scale to map letter grades to Grade Points (GP) as follows: - A+ / A: 4.00 Grade Points (Outstanding / Exceptional) - A-: 3.67 Grade Points (Very Good) - B+: 3.33 Grade Points (Good) - B: 3.00 Grade Points (Above Average) - B-: 2.67 Grade Points (Average) - C+: 2.33 Grade Points (Below Average) - C: 2.00 Grade Points (Satisfactory / Minimum Graduation Average) - C-: 1.67 Grade Points (Pass / Subject to Repetition) - D+: 1.33 Grade Points (Low Pass) - D: 1.00 Grade Points (Minimum Pass) - F: 0.00 Grade Points (Fail)  3. ACADEMIC PROBATION AND DISMISSAL RULES - MINIMUM GRADUATION REQ: To qualify for the award of a Bachelor's (BS) degree, a student must secure and maintain a minimum Cumulative Grade Point Average (CGPA) of 2.00 out of 4.00. - PROBATION TRIGGER: If a student's Cumulative CGPA falls strictly below 2.00 at the end of any regular semester, they are automatically placed on \"First Academic Probation\". - COURSE LOAD RESTRICTION: Students on active academic probation are heavily restricted in their course enrollment, typically capped at a maximum of 12 credit hours per semester to facilitate academic recovery. - DEGREE CANCELLATION: Accumulating three (3) consecutive academic warnings (remaining on probation for three consecutive regular semesters without elevating the CGPA back to 2.00) results in automatic degree cancellation and formal dismissal from the university. - COURSE REPETITION: When a student repeats a course in which they previously earned an 'F' or a low passing grade, the newly obtained grade entirely replaces the old grade in the final CGPA calculation logic.  4. UNIVERSITY DEAN'S LIST AND RECTOR'S LIST HONORS - DEAN'S LIST OF HONORS: To qualify for the prestigious Dean's List at the end of a regular semester, an undergraduate student must secure a Semester GPA (SGPA) of strictly 3.50 or higher. Additionally, they must have registered for a full-time course load (minimum 15 credit hours), maintained a minimum of 75% attendance in all courses, and have no active disciplinary or \"F\" grades. - RECTOR'S LIST OF HONORS: Awarded to students who maintain a Cumulative CGPA of 3.80 or higher continuously throughout the duration of their degree program.",
              "type": "string"
            }
          ]
        },
        "options": {}
